            {
              "id": "lesson-1-5",
              "title": "Summary & Unit Assessment",
              "type": "article",
              "duration": "15 min",
              "sections": [
                {
                  "type": "markdown",
                  "content": "## One-page summary\n\n- **Total return = income + appreciation.** Income is contractual and stable; appreciation carries the risk.\n- **Direct cap:** Value = NOI₁ / R₀, and R₀ = r − g. Falling *r* (or rising *g*) raises value.\n- **DCF** discounts each year's cash flow plus the net sale price at *r* — used for finite holds.\n- **Proforma order:** vacancy off PGI, opex off EGI, to reach NOI.\n- **Leverage** is positive when the cost of debt is below the cap rate — it lifts equity IRR (and risk)."
                },
                {
                  "type": "quiz",
                  "content": "Unit 1 Assessment",
                  "quizData": [
                    {
                      "id": "u1a-q1",
                      "text": "How is Effective Gross Income (EGI) calculated?",
                      "type": "multiple-choice",
