                        "NOI + CapEx"
                      ],
                      "correctAnswer": "PGI − Vacancy + Other Income",
                      "explanation": "EGI accounts for vacancy losses (and any other income) before operating expenses are deducted to reach NOI."
                    },
                    {
                      "id": "u1a-q2",
                      "text": "What is the Internal Rate of Return (IRR)?",
                      "type": "multiple-choice",
                      "options": [
                        "The rate where NPV = 0",
                        "The cap rate plus growth",
                        "The risk-free rate"
                      ],
                      "correctAnswer": "The rate where NPV = 0",
                      "explanation": "IRR is the single discount rate that makes the present value of the cash flows equal to the purchase price (NPV = 0)."
                    },
                    {
                      "id": "u1a-q3",
                      "text": "A mortgage at 5% is used to buy a property with a 6.5% cap rate. This is an example of:",
                      "type": "multiple-choice",
                      "options": [
                        "Positive leverage",
                        "Negative leverage",
                        "No leverage effect"
                      ],
                      "correctAnswer": "Positive leverage",
                      "explanation": "The cost of debt (5%) is below the cap rate (6.5%), so borrowing increases the return on equity — positive leverage."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
